title: For Sale:  People who panic bought please read this
postcontent:
Look, it is time to admit you made a mistake. I know your wife is gnawing on you about the credit card debt and all, but you need to face reality. You are NOT going to get any sane person to pay 33% or more over retail for your item. When you list that item for sale for that amount to "get what i have in it" back, realize that your are just prolonging your folly and anguish. 

Now, when your item does not sell for your price for weeks and you post "must sell this week. make offers", be prepared to get low end real value offers for a USED example of your gun. Also, please do not wring your hands and excoriate the guy making such an offer as a lowballer or tell him he needs to do more research on the product. He has. The market has decided the used dpms mk12 is not worth the $2000 you demand. Neither is your used Colt M4 worth $1800 to folks not panicked by legislation. 

In closing, learn to negotiate. Learn to not buy the panic. Learn to graciously say "no, thanks". Learn that a free market eventually sets a fair price, not "what you have in it".

Check out " The Handbook of Manly Virtue" on Amazon.com
